# pnpm 9 (the project's corepack-pinned version) requires CLI tools used in
# per-package `scripts` to be declared as direct devDeps of that package, not
# as root devDeps. The default strict linker creates per-package
# `node_modules/.bin/` symlinks for each package's direct devDeps, and
# `pnpm run` only adds that per-package bin to the script's PATH.
# Root-only devDeps (in package.json at the repo root) are NOT on per-package
# script PATHs. Keep the workspace's CLI tool surface in sync by declaring
# eslint, typescript, etc. as devDeps in each package that uses them.
